### 3. **Utility Functions - getParsedCurrency & getParsePoints**
**Location:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/appSemPararv3/node_modules/@semparar/mf-app-fintech-card-place/src/utils/functions.ts`

```typescript
export const getParsedCurrency = (text: string) => {
  const digits = (text || '').replace(/\D/g, '');
  const n = parseInt(digits, 10);
  if (Number.isNaN(n)) {
    return 0;
  }
  return n / 100;
};

export const getParsePoints = (text: string) => {
  const digits = (text || '').replace(/\D/g, '');
  const n = parseInt(digits, 10);
  return Number.isNaN(n) ? 0 : n;
};
```

**Purpose:**
- `getParsedCurrency`: Extracts digits from text and converts to decimal currency (dividing by 100 for cents)
- `getParsePoints`: Extracts and parses integer values from text strings

**Other Related Functions in Same File:**
- `formatToCurrency()` - Formats numbers to "R$ X,XX" format
- `getFormattedPoints()` - Formats numbers with pt-BR locale (with thousand separators)
- `formatCurrencyBR()` - Uses Intl.NumberFormat for BRL currency

